President Donald Trump delivered remarks on the American energy industry, emphasizing the importance of energy independence and dominance. He highlighted the abundance of energy resources in the United States and pledged to remove job-killing regulations and promote energy development. Trump mentioned several initiatives to boost American energy exports, including the revival of the nuclear energy sector, addressing barriers to financing overseas coal energy plants, and approving the construction of a petroleum pipeline to Mexico. He also announced that the Department of Energy will approve two long-term applications to export natural gas and create a new offshore oil and gas leasing program. Trump concluded by expressing his optimism for the future of American energy and the nation as a whole.